article_title: ObamaCare Deductibles Hit Patient Pocketbooks And Hospital Finances

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: Health plans offered on state and federal marketplaces known as exchanges mean higher deductibles and higher out-of-pocket costs for consumers and potentially less business for hospitals under the Affordable Care Act.
